Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{700%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle
over the @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the #oven{} is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}.
  Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%grams}.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the
@diced chorizo{90%grams} and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Pop a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat, stir in the browned chorizo,
@mixed beans{1%carton} along with their liquid, @tomato passata{1%carton},
@red wine stock paste{28%grams}, @chipotle paste{20%grams} (add less if you'd
prefer things milder) and the @sugar{1%tsp} for the sauce.

Bring the chipotle chilli to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until
slightly thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once the chilli has thickened, stir in the @butter{20%grams} until melted.

Season with salt and pepper. Add a splash of @water{} if you feel it needs it.

Share the potato wedges between your #serving bowls{}.

Top with the chorizo chipotle chilli.

Drizzle over the @soured cream{75%grams} and sprinkle over the cheese to finish
- wedges loaded!

Enjoy!